<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Vice-President in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 27 (Xinhua) -- US Vice-President Al Gore spoke
highly of Shanghai's environmental protection efforts during his
meeting with Shanghai Mayor Xu Kuangdi today.
</P>
<P>
Xu said that improving environment quality is the key to
Shanghai's implementation of the sustainable development strategy.
</P>
<P>
Gore arrived in China's largest industrial city in the
afternoon after winding up his visit to Xi'an, capital city of
northwest China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting, Xu told Gore that during the 9th Five-Year Plan
period from 1996 to 2000, Shanghai will devote at least 40 billion
RMB yuan to environmental protection.
</P>
<P>
The city also attaches great importance to afforestation, Xu
said, adding that a total of 100 pieces of public lands will be
planted in the city within the year.
</P>
<P>
The city has also launched a comprehensive project to harness
the heavily-polluted Suzhou River. The river will be expected to
become basically clean by the end of the century, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Gore expressed his hope that his country will have greater
economic cooperation with Shanghai and more US companies will come
to participate in the construction projects of the city, like
Pudong Airport, telecommunications, and finance. 
</P>
</TEXT>
