<HEADLINE> Myanmar's Myawaddy TV Begins Evening Telecast </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Myanmar's Myawaddy TV, a
military-run station, began its evening telecast today in addition
to its regular morning services, using a transponder of Asiasat
Satellite-2.
</P>
<P>
The transponder was leased from the Asia Satellite
Telecommunication Co Ltd of Hong Kong according to a contract
signed here last month between the Myanmar Defense Ministry and
the Hong Kong company.
</P>
<P>
The Myawaddy TV, a station next to the state-run Myanmar TV and
located some 30 kilometers north of Yangon, has started its
regular morning telecast since March 1995 via Asiasat Satellite-1.
</P>
<P>
