<HEADLINE> Chinese Ambassador Expects Early Agreement on PLA </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Ambassador Zhao Jihua, Chinese
senior representative on the Sino-British Joint Liaison Group
(JLG), today expected an early agreement on the entry into Hong
Kong of the People's Liberation Army (PLA) advance team.
</P>
<P>
He made the remarks when attending a completion ceremony for
four military projects to be used by the PLA garrison in Hong Kong
 after the handover.
</P>
<P>
It is reasonable, and the British side has also agreed, that a
limited number of PLA servicemen should enter into the territory
in advance to make preparations for the defense tasks the garrison
 will assume as of July 1, Ambassador Zhao said.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the Chinese side gave full consideration to the
British side's concerns over the question.
</P>
<P>
"I hope that the two sides reach an agreement (over the
question) as soon as possible since July 1 is around the corner,"
the ambassador said.
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the question of the right of abode after the
handover, Zhao said that it is a matter of the Chinese side.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese side has frequently contacted the British side and
Hong Kong government to seek their opinions on the question and
expected an early settlement, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
