<HEADLINE> HK Polytechnic University Honors 6 Outstanding Alumni </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Polytechnic
University (PolyU) today honored six distinguished alumni with the
Outstanding PolyU Alumni Award.
</P>
<P>
Leung Chun-ying, member of the Provisional Legislative Council
and the Executive Council of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region (HKSAR), and world-famous fashion designer Vivienne Tam,
were among the six awardees.
</P>
<P>
The award selection, held for the first time, was jointly
organized by the PolyU and the Federation of PolyU Alumni
Associations to give public recognition to distinguished graduates
of the university.
</P>
<P>
Nominees were judged on their professional accomplishments,
contributions to the community, as well as their support for the
alma mater and its alumni activities.  
</P>
