<HEADLINE> SA Women Soldiers Outnumber Elsewhere in World -- </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The South African National
Defense Force (SANDF) led the world table in gender representation
with 18.5 percent of its personnel comprsiing women, Deputy Defense
Minister Ronnie Kasrils said today.
</P>
<P>
Of all the women staff in the armed forces, about 11.5 percent were
combatants, the South African Press Association quoted Kasrils as saying
at the unveiling of the SANDF's new civic education program in the
legislative capital of Cape Town.
</P>
<P>
The statistics had been provided by an unidentified visiting
British military expert at a recent gender conference hosted by
the South African Defense Ministry, Kasrils said.
</P>
<P>
The United States, with 13 percent of women serving in its aremed
forces, took the second highest female percentage in the world, SAPA
said. enditem

