<HEADLINE> HK Exchange Fund Records Healthy Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Monetary
Authority (HKMA) today announced the audited results of the
Exchange Fund at end-1996 with total assets of the Fund up 16
percent to 534.5 billion HK dollars (68.53 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
According to the announcement, the accumulated earnings in the
Exchange Fund increased 7.9 percent from 160.1 billion HK dollars
(20.53 billion US dollars) at the end-1995 to 172.8 billion HK
dollars (22.15 billion US dollars) at the end of 1996.
</P>
<P>
An HKMA spokesman said, "The 12.7 billion HK dollars (1.63
billion US dollars) increase in accumulated earnings reflected the
result of HKMA's prudent management of the Fund at times of
volatile bond markets and a strong US dollar."
</P>
<P>
"The HKMA will maintain its prudent policy and continue to
invest the majority of the Fund's assets in fixed income
instruments," he added.
</P>
<P>
The HKMA also announced today the foreign reserve within the
Exchange Fund totaled 63.8 billion US dollars at the end of
February 1997. This represented a drop from the 65.9 billion
figure at end-January due to seasonal factors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
