<HEADLINE> HK Deposits, Loans, Advances Rise in February </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Statistics published today by
the Hong Kong Monetary Authority (HKMA) showed that both deposits
and loans and advances in Hong Kong increased during February this
year.
</P>
<P>
Total deposits rose by 2.8 percent in the month, following an
increase of 1.4 percent in January. Both Hong Kong dollar and
foreign currency deposits grew at a faster pace than in the
previous month, up 3.6 percent and 1.7 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Total loans and advances continued to expand, which grew by 2.6
percent in February, following a 0.1 percent rise in January.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong dollar and foreign currency loans rose by 5.7 percent
and 0.7 percent, respectively, during the month.
</P>
<P>
As Hong Kong dollar loans expanded at a faster pace than
deposits, the Hong Kong dollar loan-to-deposit ratio rose further
to 108.2 percent at end-February from 106.1 percent at
end-January.  
</P>
</TEXT>
