<HEADLINE> Chinese, Bolivian Presidents Hold Talks (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
President Sanchez thanked China for the economic and
technological assistance and the contribution it has made to
cooperative projects with Bolivia.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez said he hopes China would continue to involve itself in
the economic growth of Latin America, and he would like to see
Chinese invest in his country.
</P>
<P>
On the world situation, Jiang said the situation is presently
undergoing profound changes. The world is witnessing a clearer
trend of multipolarization, and developing countries have acquired
greater national strength and a more important status.
</P>
<P>
Peace and development of the world are faced with both
desirable opportunities and serious challenges, the Chinese
president said, adding that China's growth plays an important role
in enhancing peace, stability and, prosperity of Asia and the
world at large.
</P>
<P>
China is willing to work together with the whole world toward
this end, he emphasized.
</P>
<P>
China has diplomatic relations with 17 Latin American
countries. According to Jiang, its friendly cooperation with them
has been growing steadily in recent years.
</P>
<P>
China and Latin American nations are developing countries, with
the same development goals and sound basis for cooperation, he
said, adding that they have a great complementarity in economy and
huge potential in economic and technological exchanges.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he added, to develop Sino-Latin American relations
is in the interests of both sides. China hopes to expand mutually
beneficial cooperation with Latin American nations and work
together to maintain world peace, he said.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez said Bolivia, as an active member of the Andean Common
Market, will contribute its part to the cooperation between the
community and China.
</P>
<P>
Bolivia is willing to play an positive role in pushing forward
Latin America's economic links with Asia, especially with China in
the 21st century by making full use its geographic advantage,
Sanchez said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang expressed his his appreciations for this and said China
hopes to make joint efforts with the Andean Common Market to
nurture their relationship.
</P>
<P>
After the talks, the two heads of state attended the signing
ceremony of a Sino-Bolivian agreement on economic and
technological cooperation, a framework agreement of China
providing Bolivia with government discount loan, and a
complementary agreement on science and technological cooperation
in plateau animal husbandry.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the talks, President Jiang held a welcome ceremony in
honor of President Sanchez.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, officials of China's Ministry of Water Resources and
Bolivia's Ministry of Economic Development signed a memorandum on
the cooperation in sallow thorn growing at noon today.  
</P>
</TEXT>
