<HEADLINE> Chinese Communist Party Delegation Ends Visit to Slovakia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, March 27 (Xinhua) -- A delegation of the Communist Party
of China (CPC) left Slovakia for home today after a six-day visit,
reports from the Slovakian capital Bratislava said.
</P>
<P>
The delegation of the International Liaison Department of the
CPC Central Committee led by Dai Bingguo, the deputy head of the
department, made the visit at the invitation of the Movement for
Democratic Slovakia (HZDS), the biggest party in Slovakia's
coalition government.
</P>
<P>
Dai held talks with HZDS leaders including Vice-Chairman
Marian Huska during his stay.
</P>
<P>
The two parties agreed to promote bilateral friendship and
advance economic and political cooperation between the two
countries. 
</P>
</TEXT>
