<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Two Overseas Banks Launch RMB Business in Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai branches of the
Hong Kong and Shanghai Banking Corp. and the Industrial Bank of
Japan, Ltd. began the issuing of Renminbi (RMB) loans today for
the first time in the Pudong New Area of Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
Officials with the People's Bank of China said today that RMB
business by overseas banks is a major move of China's financial
sector opening to the outside world.
</P>
<P>
The move will also help promote Pudong's development and
opening-up, the officials said.
</P>
<P>
In accordance with regulations of the People's Bank of China on
pilot RMB business by overseas banks in Pudong, the Shanghai
branch of the Japanese bank provided 50 million yuan of loans to
two Shanghai-Japan joint ventures, respectively.
</P>
<P>
And the Shanghai branch of the Hong Kong bank supplied RMB
loans to a packaging company and a building materials company in
Shanghai. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
