<DOCNO> XIE19970328.0018 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Building Collapses in Fujian Province, 31 Killed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, March 27 (Xinhua) -- A residence building collapsed in
Putian City of east China's Fujian Province, leaving 31 dead and
16 seriously injured.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred on the night of March 25 at an electronic
company solely funded by a Hong Kong businessman, 110 workers were
buried in the rubble.
</P>
<P>
Following 34 hours of relief work, 79 people were rescued, with
16 seriously injured. The other 31 people died.
</P>
<P>
The building was constructed in 1994. In the afternoon of March
25, the contractor of the building Zheng Jianlin had been notified
of crevices in the walls. Zheng went to the site but made no
repairs.
</P>
<P>
After the accident, Zheng was seen nearby the collapsed
building, but fled right after, and police are busy looking for
him.
</P>
<P>
Hearing the disaster that night, the provincial government
managed effective rescue work. The direct cause of the accident is
under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
