<DOCNO> XIE19970328.0020 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> UNHCR Urges Italy to Drop Blockade of Albanian Refugees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations High Commission
for Refugees (UNHCR) envoy to Italy, Fazlul Karim, on Thursday
criticized Italy's coastal blockade designed to prevent Albanian
refugees reaching Italy by sea.
</P>
<P>
On an inspection tour of the refugee situation and talks with
local authorities, Karim criticized Italy's hard line policy and
told the press that the High Commission does not approve of this
type of blockade.
</P>
<P>
"We always ask that people in need be granted protection and to
be in a position to ask for it," he said.
</P>
<P>
Karim noted that since the beginning of the crisis in Albania
the UNHCR had asked neighboring counties to let in refugees
because of the disorder and anarchy in the Balkan nation.
</P>
<P>
The Italian government had followed this policy until a few
days ago when it decided to adopt a more hard-line position.
</P>
<P>
Karim went on to reiterate his demand that Rome recognize
temporary protection for a limited time period to those fleeing
Albania.
</P>
<P>
The current crisis in Albania stemmed from the collapse of
fraudulent investment schemes in January in which thousands of
Albanians lost their life savings.
</P>
<P>
Weeks of street protests turned violent three weeks ago when
angry protesters looted military depots in the south of the
country and took control of several towns.
</P>
<P>
The upheaval triggered an uncontrolled mass exodus of refugees
from Albania to neighboring Italy across the Adriatic Sea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
