<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Congressman Advocates Sino-US Talks and Understanding </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 27 (Xinhua) -- A US congressman said here today
that China and the United States need talks, mutual understanding,
and high-level contacts to remove their differences.
</P>
<P>
US Congressman Curt Weldon made the remark in a speech at the
Lincoln Lectureship. He came to the Fudan University at the
invitation of the university's president Yang Fujia.
</P>
<P>
Weldon said that the two countries have different social
systems and values, and there exist many differences. But the two
will finally find solutions to the differences as long as they
have frank talks instead of confrontation, mutual understanding
instead of suspicions, and maintain high-level contacts.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the United States often lacks the understanding
of views in other countries, especially in China. If American
decision-makers can know more about China's views on many issues,
the relations between the two countries will be more successful.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, he also praised China for the policies to
maintain Hong Kong's prosperity and stability, and supported the
"one China" stand of the US government, and advocated that the two
sides cooperate to boost environmental protection with technology
from national defense research.
</P>
<P>
The Lincoln Lectureship was founded by the Lincoln National
Group, an insurance institution in the US, and Fudan University
last year. Every year, well-known scholars, politicians and
entrepreneurs are invited to make speeches.  
</P>
</TEXT>
