<HEADLINE> Angola's Second Largest Oilfield Produces 10,000 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The daily output of the Zaire
oilfield, the second largest in Angola, has increased to the
present 10,000 barrels from 4,000 in March last year.
</P>
<P>
This was revealed by Angolan Petroleum Minister Albina Assis
at a press conference here today.
</P>
<P>
She said, it is expected that the daily output of the
oilfield will reach 20,000 barrels in the near future because a
new oilfield at Kingula will soon be put into production.
</P>
<P>
Several foreign petroleum firms will come to the Zaire
oilfield to develop oil, she added.
</P>
<P>
The petroleum industry is the pillar of the Angolan economy
and oil is the country's major export. However, the petroleum
industry has been destroyed seriously during a 19-year-old
civil war.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the country produces only 550,000 barrels
a day. enditem

