<HEADLINE> Beijing Wants to Join Hands with French in Environmental Protection </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Beijing's environmental
protection departments will open their doors to their French
counterparts, said Mayor Jia Qinglin today when meeting the
visiting French Minister of the Environment, Corinne Lepage.
</P>
<P>
Jia said that although some achievements have been made in the
protection of Beijing's environment, the environmental problems
remain a tough task.
</P>
<P>
"The French have a lot for us to learn in this regard, and I
hope that our cooperation in environmental protection be further
promoted and some practical projects can be signed," Jia said.
</P>
<P>
Corinne Lepage said that her agency also has strong interest to
cooperate with Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Pierre Morel, French Ambassador to China, attended the
meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
