<HEADLINE> Beijing Mayor Welcomes Support From Overseas Chinese </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Beijing Mayor expressed his hope
today that overseas Chinese and their friends will continue to
care for and support the capital city's economic development.
</P>
<P>
While welcoming an American-Chinese delegation from the US, Jia
Qinglin said that with the approach of July 1, Hong Kong will
return to her motherland. It is a big event in Chinese history,
and is anticipated by all the overseas Chinese, Jia noted.
</P>
<P>
Jia briefed guests on the city's progress over the past few
years and its development programme in the future.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his hope that the overseas Chinese will give more
support to the city's development.
</P>
<P>
Hugh H. Mo, head of the delegation said that even though they
are all distinguished people in the US, they will not forget that
they are Chinese. The development of China is the "greatest
encouragement" to them, he added.
</P>
<P>
Mo said on behalf of the delegation that they will continue to
contribute to the prosperity of China.
</P>
<P>
The delegation is here to celebrate the return of Hong Kong to
her motherland, and has participated in the activities to mark the
100-day countdown for the return.  
</P>
</TEXT>
