<HEADLINE> Italian Police Arrested Drug Traffickers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 27 (Xinhua)--An internation ring of drug
traffickers between Italy and Albania has been arrested by Italian
police on March 22, according to local police officials.
</P>
<P>
So far, 14 suspects have been arrested, and the other two are
being actively sought, while 50 kilos marijuana from Albania have
been confiscated, they said.
</P>
<P>
According to top police officials, these drugs are apparently
smuggled out of Albania into the Salento area, then transported to
Foggia which is the distribution center of hard drugs in Italy.
</P>
</TEXT>
