<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia Calls for Negotiations on Zairean Own </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 27 (xinhua) -- Zambian President Frederick Chiluba
said today that the two warring parties in Zaire should be allowed to
chose a venue and date for negotiations on their own, because only
this way the outcome of their talks will be more binding and
effective.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba made the remarks in Lome, the capital of Togo, where he
was attending the two-day special summit of the Organization African
Unity (OAU) to mediate the conflict in Zaire.
</P>
<P>
The Zambia News Agency quoted him as saying that peace in
Zaire is in sight because the two sides have shown readiness to
resort to negotiations other than fighting.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba said Zambia has no resources to effectively look after the
refugees from the war-torn country but it has the political will to
assist in every way possible.
</P>
<P>
On the issue of investor confidence, he said that the war has a
spill-over effect on Zambia but it is extremely peaceful for anybody
who wants to put up an investment.
</P>
<P>
Chiluba said ''since the war is not taking place in Zambia,
their (there) is no reason for anybody to feel insecure.''
