<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> France Urges Ceasefire in Zaire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 27 (Xinhua) -- France hopes that the ongoing
summit of the Organization of African Unity (OAU) in Lome, Togo,
could help stop fighting and start political dialogue between the
warring sides in Zaire, a French foreign ministry spokesman said
today.
</P>
<P>
On Wednesday, a Zairean government delegation and leaders of
the separatist Alliance of Democratic Forces for the Liberation of
Congo-Zaire (AFDL) held their first meeting in Lome.
</P>
<P>
"The meeting yesterday, for the first time, of an official
Zairean delegation and the AFDL, is in itself a success that can
be credited to the Lome summit," French Foreign Ministry spokesman
Jacques Rummelhardt said today.
</P>
<P>
"The future of Zaire can only be conceived on the basis of
democratic institutions created by free and fair elections,"
Rummelhardt added.
</P>
<P>
The separatist AFDL have been fighting government troops in
southern Zaire since last October. In only five months, the AFDL
have seized a quarter of the vast African country. 
</P>
