effect'' required to ''diligently'' maintain and monitor a daily time
management register for staff working under them, according to a
government memorandum.
</P>
<P>
Public Service, Labour and Social Welfare Deputy Minister
Alois Mangwende said the clocking-in system was meant to enhance
supervision of civil servants.
</P>
<P>
The system would also ensure a full-day work for civil servants
and reduce absenteeism during working hours and establish size of
lateness and early departure. enditem

