<HEADLINE> Malaria Claims 320 in Zimbabwe This Year </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Malaria has killed 320
Zimbabweans since the beginning of this year, a spokesman of the
Ministry of Health and Child Welfare said here today.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the trend showed an increase of seven
percent in the number of malaria cases. More than 185,133
malaria cases have so far been reported countrywide.
</P>
<P>
This time of the year is usually the peak period for malaria
outbreaks in Zimbabwe. Because of the recent widespread heavy rains,
which filled dams, rivers and flooded some areas, an upsurge in
mosquito breeding and malaria transmission was being experienced.
</P>
<P>
The ministry has put everything in place to control the
disease, the spokesman said. enditem


