<HEADLINE> 8th International Congress of WFPHA to be Held in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 27 (Xinhua) -- The 8th International Congress
of World Federation of Public Health Associations (WFPHA) will be held
in Arusha, Northern Tanzania from October 12 to 16 this year.
</P>
<P>
The Chairman of the Tanzania Public Health Asociation (TPHA),
Wenceslaus Kilama, told reporters here today that the congress
will draw 800 participants worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Kilama said the participants to the congress will include health
practitioners, policy and decision-makers, academicians and NGOs.
</P>
<P>
He said the theme for this year's congress is "Health in
Transition: Opportunities and Challenges", adding that the theme was
chosen after realizing that there are many changes affecting human
health, either positively or negatively.
</P>
<P>
The congress among other things will also dwell on the rapid
urbanization in developing countries which is mainly driven by a
search for better life, employment opportunities and changes in
production and marketing.
</P>
<P>
Kilama said current estimates indicate that by the year 2000,
the majority of the world population will be in urban centers and
at that time the essential social services will be greatly
inadequate.
</P>
<P>
Other sub-themes to be addressed are health polcies and the
strategy of health-for-all through primary health care, environmental
and occupational health and linkage between health and human rights.
enditem

