<HEADLINE> Egyptian Detained in Cyprus on Suspicion of Drug </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, March 27 (Xinhua) -- An Egyptian in connection with a
drug trafficking case was today remanded in custody for eight
days by Limassol District Court in Cyprus .
</P>
<P>
The suspect, identified as Mohamed Hafes Maarouf, was a cruise
ship cook of 33. He was arrested Wednesday at Limassol Harbor
after the police were tipped off that he had hashish in his
possession.
</P>
<P>
According to a police announcement, two black bags containing
the illicit substance was discovered strapped tightly against his
waist after a body search by the police. The announcement did not
say how much the substance totaled.
</P>
<P>
The police said Maarouf resisted the arrest and suffered minor
injuries while a customs officer was wounded.
</P>
<P>
The authorities concerned are investigating the information
that Maarouf brought with him narcotics to Cyprus on several
occasions.
</P>
<P>
The police told the court that they are looking for the
suspect's accomplices and are trying to determine the origin of
the drug found in Maarouf's possession. 
