<HEADLINE> Syria Denounces US Silence on Israeli Malpractices </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Syrian Vice-President Abdul
Halim-Khaddam today criticized the U.S. silence on the Israeli
government's settlement moves.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the leaders of the ruling Syrian Arab Baath
Party, Khaddam indicated that extending political support by the
U.S. at United Nations for the Israeli settlement policy
constitutes a negative element in the peace process and weakens
the U.S. role as one of co-sponsors of the peace process.
</P>
<P>
Khaddam apparently referred to the recent
start of the Israeli construction of 6,500 homes for the Jews in
Har Homa, also known as Jabal Abu Ghoneim in East Jerusalem, which
has aroused strong opposition from the Palestinians, Arab states
and other countries of the world.
</P>
<P>
Khaddam reviewed the latest developments worldwide and their
repercussions on Arab interests and basic Arab causes at this
juncture.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that peace which fails to restore Arab lands is
no more than what he called a return to chaos and instability in
the Middle East. Any agreement that involves deception of the
Arabs, he said, will not be accepted by them and will have grave
repercussions on security and stability in the region.
</P>
<P>
Khaddam praised the stance of the European Union on the peace
process which has urged Israel to commit to the terms of peace,
to withdraw from the Syrian territories up to the 1967 borders
and from all Lebanese lands, and to provide the Palestinian
people with the right of self-determination.
</P>
<P>
He called for the strengthening of Arab solidarity which will
serve as the solid grounds that guarantee Arab interests and the
restoration of Arab rights. 
</P>
</TEXT>
