<P>
BEIJING, March 28 (Xinhua) -- A fair to greet Hong Kong's
return to the motherland opened here today with Chinese Premier Li
Peng attending the ceremony.
</P>
<P>
Premier Li described the fair as very appropriate and
significant, and said that it will help the mainland people know
more about Hong Kong and understand the great significance of
late Deng Xiaoping's principle of "one country, two systems".
</P>
<P>
jointly sponsored by the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of
the State Council and the Hong Kong Branch of the Xinhua News
Agency, the fair systematically tells people from all walks of
life about Hong Kong's today and yesterday, the process of its
return to the motherland, the Chinese government's series of
principles towards Hong Kong, and Hong Kong's economic
achievements and social life.
</P>
<P>
In his opening speech, Li said it is unprecedented to use the
principle of "one country, two systems" to peacefully settle the
Hong Kong issue, which is also the Chinese government's
constructive contribution to seeking ways to solve international
disputes in the world.
</P>
<P>
The goal for implementing the principle of "one country, two
systems" is to resume sovereignty over Hong Kong and maintain its
long prosperity and stability, he said.
</P>
<P>
A law to totally reflect the principle of "one country, two
systems" is the Basic Law of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
Region, a national law. Not only Hong Kong, but all departments of
the Communist Party, government and army, all social organizations
and the people throughout the country should completely abide by
this law.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong's return constitutes the first important step in the
reunification of the motherland and will play an exemplary role in
Macao's stable transition and smooth return and even in the
settlement of the Taiwan issue, Li said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
