<HEADLINE> HK Fair to Greet Its Return to Motherland Opens (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
At present, he said, the First Chief Executive and the
Provisional Legislative Council of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) has been selected by election and
the principal officials of the Hong Kong SAR appointed.
</P>
<P>
Every piece of work for preparing the formation of the Hong
Kong SAR has been fruitful and conducted in good order, he said.
</P>
<P>
The confidence of the Hong Kong residents and the world
community in the future Hong Kong SAR has been boosting and its
society is stable and economy thriving.
</P>
<P>
Its position as an international financial, trade, shipping
center has further strengthened. "I am convinced that Hong Kong's
future under the principle of `one country, two systems' will be
surely more splendid with the concerted efforts of six million Hong
Kong compatriots and the backing of powerful motherland.
</P>
<P>
Following the speech, Li visited the fair along with other
senior officials Li Lanqing, Wei Jianxing, Wang Hanbin, Chi
Haotian, Lei Jieqiong, Qian Weichang, and Wan Guoquan.
</P>
<P>
Attending the opening ceremony and visiting the fair were Lu
Ping, director of the Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office of the
State Council, and Zhou Nan, director of the Hong Kong Branch of
the Xinhua News Agency.
</P>
<P>
Tung Chee-hwa, first chief executive of the Hong Kong SAR, some
principal officials of the Hong Kong SAR, well-known Hong Kong
personages and representatives of Hong Kong firms were also
present on the occasion.
</P>
<P>
The four-day fair has a total floor space of 10,000 square
meters, dividing into three parts, namely Hong Kong's history and
its return process; vigorous Hong Kong economy; Hong Kong people's
life including social services, public facilities, transportation
system, tourism, entertainment, food and shopping.
</P>
<P>
At the end of visiting the fair, Li told Xinhua that his
impression on the fair can be described as one sentence: Hong
Kong's future will be brighter and more splendid.  
</P>
