<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Premier Meets US House Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Premier Li Peng said here
today that disputes should not impact the development of Sino-US
relations.
</P>
<P>
Li made the remark here this afternoon when meeting with
Speaker of the US House of Representatives Newt Gingrich and his
delegation.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the number of US Congressmen visiting China is on
the rise annually, which is conducive to enhancing mutual
understanding.
</P>
<P>
He said that the US delegation has fully exchanged views with
China's National People's Congress (NPC) on setting up long-term
contacts and exchanges, which the Chinese government supports.
</P>
<P>
Li recalled that former US President Nixon opened the door of
Sino-US relations during his term, and the two countries
established diplomatic relations during Carter's term as US
President. He expressed the hope that US Republicans and Democrats
present at the meeting can make their contributions to the
improvement and development of Sino-US relations.
</P>
<P>
Noting that the US is the largest developed country and China
is the largest developing country, Li said that if China and the
US can maintain a stable and normal relationship avoiding
confrontations and strengthening dialogue and cooperation, it will
be not only in the fundamental interests of the two countries, but
also an important contribution to world peace and development.
</P>
<P>
Li pointed out that China and the US have both common points
and differences, and both should carry forward the common points
and resolve the differences through dialogues and contacts.
</P>
<P>
It does not matter if the differences can be solved at the
moment, Li said, adding that both sides should learn to seek
common ground while reserving differences, and do not let the
differences hinder the development of bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Li said that China abides by an independent foreign policy of
peace and it needs a long peaceful international environment,
especially a good relationship with its neighbors for its economic
construction, which is the key task for China.
</P>
<P>
Stressing that China adheres to a policy of good-neighborly
friendship and is enjoying good cooperative relations with all its
neighbors, Li called the so-called "China threat" as groundless,
saying that such assertion shows an ignorance or misunderstanding
about China.
</P>
<P>
China threatens no one, and does not seek "spheres of
influence", Li pointed out, noting that China is an important
factor for safeguarding world peace and stability.
</P>
<P>
After the Cold War, Li said, although the international
situation moves generally towards relaxation, the world is not yet
peaceful because there are still occurrences of regional
conflicts and other disputes, and peace and development are facing
many challenges.
</P>
<P>
Citing the world as a diversified one, Li said that every
country has the right to choose its own social system and
development mode.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his admiration for China's economic achievements,
Gingrich said that the delegation includes both Republicans and
Democrats, and they have come to enhance mutual understanding and
better US-China relations.
</P>
<P>
Noting that bilateral relations have had a great development
since the two sides signed the Shanghai Communique in 1972,
Gingrich said that if the US and China can build a stronger
relationship in the next century, it will make a great
contribution to the whole of mankind.
</P>
<P>
He went on to say that through contacts here, members of his
delegation have a better understanding about China's domestic and
foreign policies.
</P>
<P>
Gingrich said he does not believe that China will threat other
countries.
</P>
<P>
Vice-Chairman of the NPC Standing Committee Tian Jiyun attended
the meeting.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
