<HEADLINE> Jiang Zemin Attends Film Premiere </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 28 (Xinhua) -- President and Chairman of the
Central Military Commission Jiang Zemin today attended the debut
ceremony of a new film in the Great Hall of the People, and
congratulated the shooting crew for their success.
</P>
<P>
The film, named "A Great Turn", is about the history of the
People's Liberation Army's (PLA) turning from the strategic
defensive to strategic offensive during the War of National
Liberation (1945-1949).
</P>
<P>
Former leader Deng Xiaoping who died last month, was then the
political commissar of the Second Field Army then, and he played
an important role in the "Great Turn".
</P>
<P>
Liu Huaqing, vice-chairman of the Central Military Commission
and member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of
the CPC Central Committee, delivered a speech at the ceremony,
citing Deng as a military strategist and saying the film shows
Deng's brilliant image s .
</P>
<P>
He also said that Deng's staunch and revolutionary spirits as
well as his love for the people reflected in the film should be
learned by every PLA soldier today.
</P>
<P>
"All actions of the army should submit to the leadship of the
Party with Jiang Zemin at the core, and the PLA should always
belong to the Party, the people, and the socialist country," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Yu Yongbo, member of the Central Military Commission and
director of the PLA's General Political Department, chaired the
debut ceremony.  
</P>
</TEXT>
