<HEADLINE> Malaysia to Buy South African Attack Helicopter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 28 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia will purchase the
Rooivalk attack helicopter from South Africa as part of its
efforts to strengthen its air force.
</P>
<P>
The Royal Malaysian Air Force needs eight such aircraft under
its modernization plan, the Malaysian national news agency
reported today quoting Defense Minister Syed Hamid Albar.
</P>
<P>
However, the number of aircraft to be purchased would only be
determined after negotiations between the government and the
manufacturer Denel Group, the minister said.
</P>
<P>
He said Malaysia needed to look at its financial strength
before it could say how many it was going to buy.
</P>
<P>
"We'll probably purchase eight aircraft but it all depends on
the negotiation of the whole deal and this includes transfer of
technology if possible," he was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia set its eye on the Rooivalk during a helicopter
exhibition -- the Heli Asia show -- here last November, the report
said, while adding that Malaysia agreed to purchase the attack
helicopter after South African President Nelson Mandela's visit to
Malaysia early this month.  
</P>
</TEXT>
