<HEADLINE> New Political Party Formed in Somali Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, March 28 (Xinhua) -- A new political organization,
the United Peace Party (UPP), was formed in the Somali capital
yesterday.
</P>
<P>
The members of the party are mostly intellectuals,
businessmen, artists and youth.
</P>
<P>
UPP Chairman Abdi Muhumad Amin, a popular play composer in
Somalia, told reporters here today that the UPP is not a clannish
or regional-based party and it will work on the basic principles
of improving the Islamic religion.
</P>
<P>
Amin said his party maintains sympathizers of the two
warring parties in Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
According to the UPP Constitution, the party is designed to
promote peace in the wartorn Horn of Africa country.
</P>
<P>
The UPP is not armed and opposes the use of all kinds of
weapons for securing a political position and power, Amin said.
</P>
<P>
Amin added his party considers the unity and territorial
integrity of Somalia as sacred and non-negotiable.
</P>
<P>
Amin declared his party will play a major role in the
reconciliation between the warring parties in Somalia and in the
reconstruction of the country.
</P>
<P>
The party opposes the tribal-based theories and the clan
discrimination, he said.
</P>
<P>
This is the first non-armed political party in Mogadishu since
the last ruling political party of Somalia, the Somali Youth
League, was overthrown by Somalia's late dictator, Mohamed S.
Barre, in 1969.
</P>
<P>
Amin has composed many plays since l991 when a civil war broke
out in Somalia. Most of his plays speaks for the possible ways
of making peace in the country. Some of his plays were put on
display during meetings by Somalia's armed factions in Addis
Ababa and Nairobi.
</P>
<P>
Amin is the composer of the well-known play "Land Cruiser"
performed during the last months of late Siad Barre's regime in
Mogadishu. The play accused the late regime of buying expensive
vehicles such as Land Cruisers and begging maize from donor
countries. The play attracted all the Somalis. However, Amin
gained deep animosity from the Siad Barre regime, which was
hunting him even during its last days in power in 1991. Enidtem

=03281434

=03281441
NNNN
22:39 22:39 g # PAB
</P>
</TEXT>
