<HEADLINE> NPC Vice-Chairman Meets US House Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 28 (Xinhua) -- China and the United States
should view their relationship from strategic heights, and look
into the future, as well as seek common ground while reserving
differences.
</P>
<P>
Tian Jiyun, vice-chairman of China's National People's Congress
(NPC) Standing Committee, made the remark during a meeting with
Speaker of the US House of Representatives Newt Gingrich.
</P>
<P>
On behalf of the NPC Standing Committee Chairman Qiao Shi, who
is currently on his visit abroad, Tian extended a welcome to Newt
Gingrich, saying that Sino-US relations have improved recently,
and such ties have enjoyed good opportunities for further
improvement.
</P>
<P>
Tian noted that Newt Gingrich attaches importance to developing
bilateral ties, and shows his good wishes to establish and advance
friendly ties between the US Congress and the NPC.
</P>
<P>
"We welcome and appreciate this," Tian said.
</P>
<P>
Tian also expressed the hope that the legislatures of both
countries should expand their exchanges and increase mutual
understanding.
</P>
<P>
More contacts and dialogues between the congresses of the two
countries will help find their points in common, he said.
</P>
<P>
Newt Gingrich said the US and China can cooperate in many
areas, adding that this will promote the development of bilateral
friendly ties.
</P>
<P>
He said he hopes that the programs for setting up parliamentary
specific exchanges between the two countries would be carried out.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Tian forwarded a letter from Qiao to Newt
Gingrich, who also heard a briefing on the progress that the NPC
has made in its legislation and election, as well as the building
of China's socialist democracy and legal system.
</P>
<P>
Newt Gingrich arrived here Thursday at the invitation of the
NPC's Standing Committee. 
</P>
