<HEADLINE> Vice-Premier Meets HK Trade Promotion Team </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Vice-Premier Li Lanqing
met with a delegation from the Hong Kong Trade Development Council
(TDC) here today, saying that the TDC should strengthen its role
as the bridge between economic and trade circles in the mainland
and Hong Kong so as to promote their simultaneous development.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting in Zhongnanhai, the headquarters of the
Chinese central government, Li said that the Chinese government
will unswervingly adhere to the "one country, two systems," "Hong
Kong people governing Hong Kong," and "high degree of autonomy"
principles in dealing with Hong Kong. This is the guarantee for
the continuous stability and prosperity of the region, he said.
</P>
<P>
Li said that full implementation of the Basic Law of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR) and the principal
policies of the central government depends on the joint effort of
both sides.
</P>
<P>
Expressing his deep impression of the Hong Kong Fair held by
the TDC in Beijing, he wished the organization's activities in the
capital city all success.
</P>
<P>
Briefing the guests on reform and opening up in the mainland
and the central government's policies over Hong Kong, he said that
economic development in the mainland provides huge economic and
trade opportunities for Hong Kong. He said that the two places
should further enhance cooperation in the hi-tech field and on
projects in the central and western parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Head of the delegation, TDC Chairman Victor Fung said expressed
gratitude to Li for the central government's support to TDC's
activities in the mainland. He said that the business circles in
Hong Kong are fully confident of the territory's future
development.
</P>
<P>
Fung said that TDC will focus on promoting the significance of
the "one country, two systems" policy and introduce Hong Kong's
advantages in service, infrastructure, and international trade
connections to the mainland people.
</P>
<P>
Denise C. Y. Yue, deputy head of the delegation and Secretary
for Trade and Industry of the Hong Kong Government, said that Hong
Kong public servants give full credence to the central
government's policy of "Hong Kong people governing Hong Kong" and
"high degree of autonomy."
</P>
<P>
We will work to create favorable conditions for economic and
trade cooperation between Hong Kong and the mainland, she said.
</P>
<P>
TDC is a statutory body of the region responsible for promoting
and developing Hong Kong's trade. The TDC delegation is here at
the invitation of the Chinae Council for the Promotion of
International Trade (CCPIT).  
</P>
</TEXT>
