<HEADLINE> Mongolian Presidential Candidates Officially Announced </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ULAN BATOR, March 28 (Xinhua) -- Three candidates will run in
Mongolia's second direct presidential election on May 18,
including the current president Punsalmaagiyn Ochirbat, the
Mongolian Presidential Election Commission announced today.
</P>
<P>
Ochirbat, 55, has been nominated as the candidate of the ruling
Democratic Union Coalition, made up of the Mongolian National
Democratic Party (MNDP) and Social Democratic Party (SDP).
</P>
<P>
Ochirbat, who was elected the country's first president in 1990
by the parliament, won Mongolia's first direct presidential
election in June 1993 with 57.8 percent of the vote.
</P>
<P>
He ran as a candidate for the then opposition MNDP and SDP
after leaving the former communist Mongolian People's
Revolutionary Party (MPRP).
</P>
<P>
The MPRP's candidate for the May 18 election is Nachagyn
Bagbandy, 47, who was chairman of the Great Hural (parliament)
between July 1992 and July 1996.
</P>
<P>
Zhambyn Gombozhab, who resigned from the MPRP on March 17 to
join the Mongolian Traditional Unification Party, which has one
seat in parliament, has been nominated as the party's candidate.
</P>
<P>
Under Mongolian law, candidates can offically start their
election campaign from today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
