<HEADLINE> CPPCC Chairman Meets Bolivian President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 28 (Xinhua) -- Li Ruihuan, chairman of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC)
National Committee, told Bolivian President Gonzalo Sanchez de
Lozada that China will adhere to late leader Deng Xiaoping's
theory of building socialism with Chinese characteristics.
</P>
<P>
The last 18 years have witnessed great changes within China
since the country began the reform and opening-up drive, which has
brought concrete benefit to Chinese people, Li said.
</P>
<P>
Therefore, he noted, Deng's theory and relevant policies and
principles are very popular and the Chinese people sincerely
cherish the memory of Deng by safeguarding unity and stability.
</P>
<P>
He said that Chinese people are confident about carrying
forward the cause initiated by Deng.
</P>
<P>
Li also expressed his satisfaction with the smooth development
of the Sino-Bolivian ties, saying that the two countries share
each other's views on many international issues.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his appreciation for Bolivia's position of
sticking to the one China policy and not to have official ties
with Taiwan.
</P>
<P>
Sanchez spoke highly of China's great economic achievements,
saying that the future of the world is closely connected with
China's stability and development.
</P>
<P>
He stressed that all developing countries need a peaceful and
stable international environment for development.  
</P>
</TEXT>
