</P>
<P>
-- President Clinton's Middle East envoy, Dennis B. Ross, met
with Yasir Arafat in Morocco and then flew to Israel for talks
with Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu. The key issues, one
official said, are security and terrorism for both Israel and
Palestinians. Madeleine K. Albright may make her first trip to the
region as Secretary of State if it can bring both sides back to
the table.
</P>
