<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Interviewees Refute Involvement in US Political Donations (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 28 (Xinhua) -- In a recent period, the media in
the United States have been spreading the news about China's
alleged involvement in political donations to the Democratic
National Party.
</P>
<P>
To verify the truth and notify the world of facts, Xinhua
reporters has conducted interviews with responsible persons of
the three units mentioned in the media reports, namely, the China
Council for the Promotion of International Trade, the China
International Trust and Investment Corporation (CITIC), and the
China Ocean Shipping Corporation.
</P>
<P>
The US media claimed the three units have been involved in the
case of political donations. By doing so, they are taking aim at
the Chinese government.
</P>
<P>
Wang Jun, president of the CITIC, told Xinhua that the US media
has recently fabricated some slanderous stories about CITIC and
himself. "These stories maliciously distorted the facts occuring
during my tour in the US this February, saying that I participated
in the activity concerning the illegal political donations to the
US president. I deem it is necessary to clarify this," he said.
</P>
<P>
According to Wang, from February 2 to 9, 1996, as president of
the CITIC, he visited the US at the invitation of the Lehman
Brothers Company of the US. The main purpose of the tour was to
acquaint himself with the US bond market and also US investors'
attitude toward the Asian market, particularly, the Chinese
market, as the CITIC hopes to maintain sound and cooperative
relations with US investors.
</P>
<P>
Wang's agenda included a meeting with the late Ron Brown,
secretary of the U.S. Department of Commerce. In the interview,
the Chinese side mainly explained the CITIC's business operations,
and hoped to expand the Sino-US trade, especially the CITIC's
imports from the US.
</P>
<P>
Over the past several years, the CITIC has not only set up its
sound cooperative relations with the US economic community, but
also maintained friendly exchanges with well-known figures who
took positions in the US political circle. The CITIC has worked to
promote the economic and technological cooperation and exchanges
between China and the US.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
