<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets US Senators </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese President Jiang Zemin met
with three Senators from the United States here today, saying that
the maintenance and development of a healthy and stable Sino-US
relationship is not only beneficial to the economic growth and the
people of the two big countries, but also to the peace and
development of the world.
</P>
<P>
"We are glad to witness that more and more members of the US
congress are supportive of developing relations with China," he
said.
</P>
<P>
Jiang met with Senators Connie Mack, James Jeffords and Joseph
Lieberman in Zhongnanhai, the headquarters of the Chinese central
government.
</P>
<P>
Briefing the guests on the Chinese government's policy on Hong
Kong, he said that the government will ensure "Hong Kong people
governing Hong Kong" and high degree of autonomy in the region
under the principle of "one country, two systems."
</P>
<P>
Mack said that on his first trip to China, he and the other
senators are deeply impressed by the country's economic
achievement.
</P>
<P>
He said that he fully understands the significance of Hong
Kong's return to China. He wished the region stability and
prosperity in the future.
</P>
<P>
Lieberman said that there is a growing number of US
congressmen, regardless of their party, who believe that the
Sino-US relations will be the most important bilateral relations
in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
The two countries have good reason to develop a sound bilateral
relationship and make it a stable and constructive one, he added.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
