<HEADLINE> Two Dead, 20 Missing In Norway Avalanche </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 28 (Xinhua) -- Two mountain climbers were
killed by an avalanche in north Norway and about 20 skiers were
missing in snowy weather around the country, according to local
reports on Friday.
</P>
<P>
The climbers, both men at their 30s, were reported missing on
Thursday and a Red Cross team with dogs found them buried in an
avalanche on Friday.
</P>
<P>
They were the first victims of snowy weather during the
Easter holiday in the Scandinavian country.
</P>
<P>
Norwegians traditionally spend Easter skiing in the mountains
while this year the holiday was spoiled by the bad weather.
</P>
<P>
Searches launched at the weekend have so far rescued dozens of
missing people. 
</P>
</TEXT>
