<DOCNO> XIE19970328.0094 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Manila Eyes Labor Accords to Protect Overseas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 28 (Xinhua) -- Philippine President Fidel Ramos
today said he has directed the Labor Department to forge bilateral
labor agreements with various countries to protect the welfare and
rights of Filipino Overseas Workers.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said during an inspection tour to the Subic Bay Freeport
that he was optimistic that labor accords will soon be reached
with the countries hosting overseas Filipinos following the
signing of the Philippines-Qatar Labor Agreement.
</P>
<P>
The labor accord which forged on March 9 during Ramos' state
visit to Qatar was the first ever between the Philippines and a
Gulf state.
</P>
<P>
Under the agreement, Qatar and the Philippines will lay down
the necessary rules and regulations on the implementation of the
accord.
</P>
<P>
The agreement also stipulates that recruitment of workers from
the Philippines, their entry into and employment in Qatar will be
regulated by relevant laws, rules and procedures of the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
The President said he has already tasked the Department of
Labor and Employment to make sure similar agreements to be forged
with other countries to ensure the well-being of overseas
Filipinos.
</P>
<P>
He added that the government will not stop searching for ways
and taking advantage of every opportunity to give every Filipino
expatriate worker the full protection he deserves.
</P>
<P>
Ramos said that whatever problem may arise involving a Filipino
worker would be dealt with expeditiously through the mechanism of
the labor accord between the Philippines and the country hosting
overseas Filipinos. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
