<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Gore Arrives In Seoul For Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, March 28 (Xinhua) - U.S. Vice President Al Gore flew
into Seoul from Shanghai today for talks expected to focus on
efforts to launch peace negotiations on the Korean peninsula.
</P>
<P>
Gore is due to meet with Prime Minister Koh Kun on Friday night
and with President Kim Young-Sam on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
A central part of Gore's mission is to coordinate US and South
Korean policy towards the Democratic People's Republic of Korea
and to try to bring the DPRK into four-nation peace talks with
South Korea, China and the U.S.
</P>
<P>
The talks are aimed at securing a lasting peace on the
peninsula to replace the armistice that ended the 1950-1953 Korean
war.
</P>
<P>
Gore, on the third and last leg of a visit through Northeast
Asia that took him to Japan and China, is scheduled to leave for
Washington late Saturday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
