<HEADLINE> Germany's SAP Keen on China Application Software Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 28 (Xinhua) -- Germany's SAP company, the
world's largest supplier of standard application software, hopes
that its business managment system R/3 will occupy as much as 40
percent share of China's application software market by the turn
of the century.
</P>
<P>
Claus M. Zimmer, managering director of SAP Greater China, told
a news conference here today about SAP's development plans in
China.
</P>
<P>
R/3 system, which is developed for business resource planning,
is the most popular software of its kind in the world and accounts
for 38 percent share of the worldwide market. Application of the
system can give a greater improvement to enterprises management
covering personnel, production, marketing, financial, accounting,
and assets sectors, explained Zimmer.
</P>
<P>
SAP has supplied the R/3 system to more than 20 noted big
foreign-funded enterprises in China, which involves in
automobiles, manufacturing, hi-tech, iron and steel, retail sales,
and consulting sectors.
</P>
<P>
During the coming three years, SAP will focus on China's on big
state enterprises, especially those in the fields of electronics,
petrochemicals, airport, consumers' goods, automobiles, and
tobacco.
</P>
<P>
SAP, which is the fifth largest independent software supplier
worldwide, got 486 million deutsche marks in sales in the
Asia-Pacific Region last year, rising 67 percent over the previous
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
