<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, April 28 (Xinhua) -- Canadian Adham Sharara is
expected to challenge Chinese Xu Yinsheng as president of the
International Table Tennis Federation (ITTF).
</P>
<P>
Sharara, first vice president of the ITTF, will very likely bid
for the top position at the table tennis ruling body, Xu said here
on Friday.
</P>
<P>
"Sharara has once told me he will publicize an open letter to
inform all continental table tennis federations that he won't bid
for ITTF president at the ITTF Congress during the world
championships in Manchester, but I haven't received this letter,"
said Xu, who succeeded deceased president Lollo Hammarlund in
December 1995.
</P>
<P>
"I assume that he will challenge me," added Xu.
</P>
<P>
Sharara, also general-secretary of the Canadian table tennis
association, is in charge of the sport's marketing in the ITTF.
</P>
<P>
"I am confident I will get more votes than Sharara in the
reelection," Xu said. 
