<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Scholars on Dalai's Taiwan Trip </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 28 (Xinhua) -- The Dalai Lama's so-called
"religious pilgrimage" to Taiwan island is a political crusade
under the guise of religion, and an activity to split the
motherland made by the forces advocating "Taiwan independence" and
"Tibet independence," two Chinese scholars said here today.
</P>
<P>
In an interview with Xinhua, Li Yihu and Xu Bodong, professors
from Beijing University and its branch school, said that as Hong
Kong will soon return to the embrace of its motherland, China's
reunification is the trend of the times and reflects the
aspiration of the people.
</P>
<P>
The separatist activities of the Taiwan authorities and the
Dalai clique will surely end in failure, as they are opposed by
the entire Chinese people, including the Taiwan compatriots and
compatriots of ethnic Tibetan group, the scholars emphasized.
</P>
<P>
Prof. Li said the Dalai Lama is not an ordinary religious
figure, but rather a political leader of the separatist forces in
Tibet.
</P>
<P>
Lee Teng-hui, Taiwan's supreme ruler, is a political leader of
another form of separatist forces, he noted.
</P>
<P>
The meeting between Lee Teng-hui and the Dalai Lama, held in
the name of "spiritual reform" and "humanitarianism," was actually
a coming-together of the two separatist forces in a move to change
their unfavorable situation, Li noted.
</P>
<P>
Prof. Xu said the forces of "Taiwan independence" and "Tibet
independence" have similar concepts of splitting the country, and
the Taiwan authorities' purpose to collude with the Dalai Lama is
to challenge the peaceful reunification.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, they want to make use of the Dalai's international
connections to put forth their repeatedly blocked "pragmatic
diplomacy" and expand the international scope of the "Taiwan
independence" movement, Xu said.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Taiwan authorities are catering to the need of
the anti-China forces worldwide to pave the way for further
collusion, he said.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the two scholars said, the Dalai's Taiwan trip is a
very dangerous step the Taiwan authorities has taken on its way of
splitting the motherland, fully exposing the Taiwan authorities'
real attempt to contend with the "one China" principle and
deteriorate the cross-straits relations, and the true feature of
the Dalai Lama who passes himself off as the religious figure.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
