<HEADLINE> UN to Finance Liberia's Reconstruction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 28 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations has approved
six projects involving about 500,000 U.S. Dollars for Liberia's
post-war reconstruction.
</P>
<P>
A report reaching here today quoted the U.N. Department of
Humanitarian Affairs (UNDHA) as saying that a good number of
projects would be handled by local non-governmental agencies in
Liberia.
</P>
<P>
A majority of the projects are already being implemented with
nine projects having reached advance stages of implementation,
the U.N. agency said on Thursday in Monrovia, the capital of
Liberia.
</P>
<P>
It said the projects, short-term and community-based, are
designed to help former combatants and war-affected persons
return to civil life in post-war Liberia.
</P>
<P>
Currently, a total of 17 projects funded by UNDHA are being
undertaken by international non-governmental groups in the
country. 
</P>
