<DOCNO> XIE19970328.0115 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Japanese Swimmer Sets Short-Course Swimming World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TOKYO, March 28 (Xinhua) -- Ayari Aoyama of Japan set a women's
100 meters butterfly short-course world record at a junior
national swimming meet here on Friday.
</P>
<P>
Aoyama, now 15, was timed 58.24 seconds, beating the previous
world record by 0.05 seconds. The previous record was set last
December by Misty Hyman of the United States.
</P>
<P>
Aoyama became the first Japanese swimmer to break a world
record in 25 years since Mayumi Aoki took the women's 100-meter
butterfly gold medal at the 1972 Munich Olympic Games with a
winning time of one minute 3.34 seconds. 
</P>
</TEXT>
