<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Stock Exchange Achieves Bumper Half Results: Report </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 28 (Xinhua) -- The Stock Exchange of Hong Kong
has had a bumper first half of the current financial year with a
lot of new issues with its net surplus up to 64.7 million HK
dollars (8.35 million US dollars), 12 times over the same period
of 1995.
</P>
<P>
According to a report from the stock exchange, during the six
months ending December 1996, 32 new issues listed on the market,
raising 18.5 billion HK dollars (2.39 billion US dollars).
</P>
<P>
A further 49 debt securities were issued during the period
worth 63.9 billion HK dollars (8.25 billion US dollars), while 176
warrant issues comprising 49 equity warrants and 127 derivative
warrants were also issued.
</P>
<P>
Turnover during the six months amounted to 299.3 million HK
dollars (38.62 million US dollars), an increase of 101.9 million
HK dollars (13.15 million US dollars) or 51.6 percent
year-on-year.
</P>
<P>
Total market capitalization during the period increased 48
percent over last year to 3.476 trillion HK dollars (448.5 billion
US dollars), making the exchange the 7th largest in the world
compared to its eight position at the end of 1995.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
