<HEADLINE> China's Township Enterprises Growing Smoothly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 28 (Xinhua) -- China's township enterprises
maintained a rapid growth rate of 15.7 percent in the past two
months over the same period last year, latest statistics from the
Ministry of Agriculture show.
</P>
<P>
During the January-February period, these firms completed
industrial output of 105.9 billion yuan, said today's China
Township Enterprises Daily.
</P>
<P>
The Beijing-based newspaper said that the sales volume of these
firms increased by 16.1 percent to reach 429.8 billion yuan during
the period on a year-on-year base.
</P>
<P>
The ratio of sales to production reached 91.19 percent, higher
than in last year.
</P>
<P>
The newspaper also noted that the township enterprises now
enjoy a larger part in the country's industrial output,
indicating the increasing strength of the firms.
</P>
<P>
Firms in eastern China are still operating better than in the
middle and western parts. Sales to production ratio of the firms
in the three parts were 91.9 percent, 89.2 percent and 88 percent
respectively. 
</P>
</TEXT>
