<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> HK Jockey Club Donates Funds to Help Prisoners' Study </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 28 (Xinhua) -- The Hong Kong Jockey Club has
donated three million HK dollars (387,100 US dollars) to the
Correctional Services Department (CSD) to help hundreds of
prisoners to further improve their language skills.
</P>
<P>
The donation is to be used for building two language
laboratories at Stanley Prison and a multi-media language
laboratory at Lai King Training Center, a CSD spokesman said here
today.
</P>
<P>
Two language laboratories at Stanley Prison will be built at a
cost of about 1.6 million HK dollars (206,460 US dollars) and they
are scheduled to be completed within the next six months, he said.
</P>
<P>
The labs will enable 20 prisoners at a time to learn various
languages through audio-visual equipment.
</P>
<P>
The multi-media language laboratory at Lai King Training Center
that will accommodate 24 inmates per session is expected to be
completed in five months at a cost of about 1.3 million HK dollars
(167,700 US dollars).
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that most inmates admitted to Lai King
Training Center, which has a population of about 300, are
characterized by their low educational level, especially in both
Chinese and English language ability because of their early drop
out from school.
</P>
<P>
He said that the inadequacy in language ability is a major
hindrance for them to attain better chances of employment or
further schooling, which in turn makes it difficult for them to
lead a decent and industrious life after their discharge from the
center.
</P>
<P>
He said that a properly equipped language laboratory with
modern teaching equipment is considered essential in providing
inmates with proper language training.
</P>
<P>
Since its first donation of 130,000 HK dollars (16,774 US
dollars) in 1979, the Hong Kong Jockey Club Charities Trust has
donated more than 31 million HK dollars (four million US dollars)
to CSD for the project.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
