<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-28 11:20 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> OIC Head Calls for Support of Jerusalem Cause </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TUNIS, March 28 (Xinhua) -- Secretary General of the
Organisation of Islamic Conference (OIC) Izzidine Iraki called
Thursday night upon the OIC members to extend all forms of
consolidation and support to the Palestinians in their fight
against Israel over Jerusalem in view of the grave perils
befalling the holy city, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the 16th session of the OIC Jerusalem Committee in
the Moroccan capital city of Rabat, he said the OIC members should
back the cause of Jerusalem "particularly that the coming phase
will witness the commencement of the final status negotiations
between the Palestine Liberation Organization (PLO) and Israel.
</P>
<P>
He asserted the need "to materialize the Islamic nation's
support of this top issue and to confront the settlement offensive
and the Judaization policy to which Jerusalem is being exposed."
</P>
<P>
Jerusalem is engaged in a struggle against time to offset
Judaization, obliteration and forgery, he said.
</P>
<P>
The OIC chief underscored that the gravity of the situation
necessitated an official as well as popular stances and the
mobilization of Islamic moral and material potentials for this
purpose.
</P>
<P>
He criticized the Israeli hardline government for trying to
isolate Jerusalem geographically, politically, economically and
socially by putting up barricades at the northern, southern and
eastern entrances, and prohibiting the entry of Palestinians
living beyond it.
</P>
<P>
Beside isolating the city internationally, the Israeli
government is denying foreign diplomats and officials the right to
visit the "Orient House", the Palestinian political symbol in
Jerusalem, he said.
</P>
<P>
The OIC Jerusalem committee, meeting in Rabat at foreign
ministerial level under the chairmanship of Moroccan King Hassan,
has concluded its works last evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
