<HEADLINE> Tax Reform to Help Increase Revenue: Pak PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 28 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif said here today that his economic reform package would help
increase revenue generation.
</P>
<P>
The tax reform would plug tax evasion and widen the tax-base,
Sharif said at a news conference here, adding that the higher tax
rates had entailed tax evasion to a larger extent.
</P>
<P>
Lower tax rates would provide incentive to the people to pay
their taxes, he said, and the government expected higher income
from taxes after the implementation of the economic revival
program.
</P>
<P>
When answering a question, the Prime Minister also said his
government would overhaul tax collection system in the country.
</P>
<P>
The government will take necessary action within the next 60
days to revamp the system which is beset with corruption, he said.
</P>
<P>
