<HEADLINE> Chinese Vice-Premier Meets US House Speaker </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 28 (Xinhua) -- China hopes the current visit by
Speaker of the US House of Representatives Newt Gingrich will
"help deepen mutual understanding between China and the US and
strengthen mutual trust."
</P>
<P>
Chinese Vice-Premier Zhu Rongji made the remark during a
meeting with Gingrich and his party, in which Zhu described the
house speaker's China visit as an important step in the Sino-US
relationship.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said the development of the bilateral relations should be
based on mutual understanding, respect and trust.
</P>
<P>
He also briefed the US visitors on China's reforms and opening
up policy and its economic development.
</P>
<P>
Gingrich, who is the second US house speaker to visit China
since the two countries forged diplomatic ties, said China's
economic development and the improvement of the Chinese people's
living standard are two of the greatest achievements of mankind in
the last two decades.
</P>
<P>
The US congress and the American people are "seeking long-term
and stable relations" with China and trying to "avoid ups and
downs," Gingrich said.
</P>
<P>
He said his delegation, which was made of 12 congressmen, would
try to acquire more knowledge about China through this trip so as
to make contributions to the growth of the bilateral relations.
</P>
<P>
Liu Huaqiu, director of the Foreign Affairs Office under
China's State Council, and Zhu Qizhen, vice-chairman of the
Foreign Affairs Committee of China's National People's Congress
(NPC) attended the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Gingrich arrived in Beijing on March 27 at the invitation of
the Standing Committee of the NPC.  
</P>
</TEXT>
