<HEADLINE> Mao Mausoleum to Be Repaired, Stop Receiving Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 28 (Xinhua) -- The Chairman Mao Memorial Hall
will be repaired next month through the end of this year, and will
stop receiving visitors during this period, the Management Bureau
of this building said in an announcement here today.
</P>
<P>
The Mausoleum was completed in May, 1977. Since its opening to
the public on September 9 of that year, 110 million people have
visited the hall to pay their respects to the late Chinese leader,
the announcement states.
</P>
<P>
The building and its interior facilities need fixing after 20
years' use. Central authorities said the reparations will begin on
April 1 and conclude on December 31.
</P>
<P>
Visitation will be prohibited as a safety precaution, the
announcement says.  
</P>
</TEXT>
