<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambian Bank Suffers in Massive Fraud </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, March 28 (Xinhua) -- The First Alliance Bank in Ndola,
capital of Zambia's Copperbelt Province, has been swindled out of
800 million Kwacha, according to the local press today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted bank officials as saying that the missing
money had been deposited at the bank by one of their clients in
the form of 400,000 U.S. Dollars before it was stolen.
</P>
<P>
It was reported that police and bank officials received a
report about the massive fraud on Thursday and they questioned
some of the bank employees and a businessman from Mufulira over
the case.
</P>
<P>
The fraud is said to have shaken the bank's directors who now
have a task of filling the gap in the coffers.
</P>
<P>
There are a number of bank frauds reported every year in
Zambia.
</P>
<P>
Copperbelt police chief Alexander Makayi said that bank cases
are usually very difficult because most of the banks always want
to solve such scandals internally without involving police.
</P>
</TEXT>
