<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, March 28 (Xinhua) -- Three people were killed and two
missing when a bus crashed Thursday evening into a river from a
bridge in South Korea's southern city Pusan, the Yonhap News
Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
The report quoted the only survivor as saying that a loud bang
of collision was heard when the bus was driving at high speed on a
bridge over the Radong River.
</P>
<P>
Police and rescuers tried for two and a half hours to pull the
bus out, finding one alive and three dead.
</P>
<P>
Police said the two missing, including the driver, may have
been washed away by the current.
</P>
<P>
They said speeding may have caused the crash. 
