<DOCNO> XIE19970328.0149 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spectacular Harbor Parade Starts HK-Osaka Tall Ship Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 28 (Xinhua) -- A spectacular tall ship parade
through the Victoria Harbor here on Friday marked the official
start of the Sail Osaka '97 Tall Ship Race which ends in Osaka,
Japan, in late April.
</P>
<P>
Taking part in the parade were 32 tall ships with a crew of
more than 1,500 youths from 18 countries and Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Accompanied by more than 50 yachts and other boats, the ships
created a rare scene when they lined up in Hong Kong's major
waterway. They then set sail east of Waglan Island for the Race,
the first ever to be held in the North Pacific.
</P>
<P>
The parade attracted thousands of local residents and tourists
to the banks of the harbor. Some came as early as seven o'clock
in the morning to take up vantage points for snap shots.
</P>
<P>
The race is co-organized by Hong Kong's Marine Department and
Urban Council with the support of the Hong Kong Tourist
Association, and Orient Overseas Container Line Limited.
</P>
<P>
The race from Hong Kong to Osaka will have stopovers in Okinawa
and Kagoshima with two races. The first race is from Hong Kong to
Okinawa, with a finishing time limit of April 10. It will be
followed by a cruise-in-company from Okinawa to Kagoshima and a
second race from Kagoshima to the final destination Osaka, with a
finishing time limit of April 27. 
</P>
</TEXT>
