<HEADLINE> China to Hold Nationwide Book Fair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, March 28 (Xinhua) -- China will hold a nationwide
book fair this August in Changchun, northeast China's Jilin
Province, an event widely anticipated by Chinese press and
publication circles.
</P>
<P>
The Eighth National Book Fair, approved by the State
Administration of Press and Publication, will be co-sponsored by
the provincial authority and the city government, together with
local press and publication bureaus and the Xinhua Bookstore.
</P>
<P>
"The event will play an important role in the country's
cultural and ethical progress and economic development," said vice
governor Sang Fengwen, who is also the director of the fair's
organizing committee.
</P>
<P>
On exhibit will be books, journals and audio-video products
published last year, and some books from HK and Taiwan will also
available, he said.
</P>
<P>
Some 3,100 publishing houses, bookstores, or companies dealing
with publication-related business will bring over 103,000 kinds of
books, journals and electronic publications.
</P>
<P>
And 2,000 purchasing groups will come to the fair, which is
expected to have an estimated 1.2 million visitors, according to
the sponsor.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, several book shows are to be held in local counties
and villages to meet the demand of rural readers.  
</P>
