<HEADLINE> Zairean Soldiers Join Ugandan Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 28 (Xinhua) -- Some 200 Zairean government
soldiers have joined the remnants of the Allied Democratic Forces
(ADF) rebels in western Uganda, the New Vision paper reported
today.
</P>
<P>
Citing an intelligence officer in Ugandan army on Tuesday, the
paper said the Zairean soldiers have arrived in Rwenzori
Mountains in western Kasese district, settled down and joined the
ADF.
</P>
<P>
The Zairean soldiers were monitored by local people friendly
to Ugandan authorities when they passed eastern Zaire with their
arms and ammunition.
</P>
<P>
The 200 Zairean soldiers are believed to be survivors under
offensives of Banyamulenge rebels in eastern Zaire and to be
still loyal to Mobutu Sese Seko, the ailing Zairean president.
</P>
<P>
The main forces of ADF were annihilated since it crossed into
western Uganda last November, and its remnants split into small
groups scattering in the west and southwest of Uganda. 
</P>
