<HEADLINE> Steel Giant Debuts in Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, March 28 (Xinhua) -- The Tangshan Steel Co. Ltd.
floated nearly 1.1 billion yuan-worth (about 132.5 million US
dollars) of new stocks Thursday, the biggest sum ever raised by a
listed company in Shenzhen Stock Exchange.
</P>
<P>
The steel venture placed 120 million A shares in total, at a
per share value of 9.22 yuan.
</P>
<P>
"Our company will use the funds raised for technical
renovations, and the completion of such projects will raise our
annual production capacity from the current 2.1 million to three
million tons," a company official told Xinhua.
</P>
<P>
The steel company ranked tenth in China's steel industry last
year, but its annual profit came in sixth. Faced with the sliding
economic efficiency in the national steel-making sector last year,
the company realized 430 million yuan in net profit.
</P>
<P>
The official also said that golden opportunities still await
Chinese steel-makers, since the market demand for high-quality
steel has been on the rise.
</P>
<P>
China has been importing steel since the 1980s, between 20 to
30 million tons annually.  
</P>
