<HEADLINE> Nepal Needs Technology Transfer for Industrialization: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, March 28 (Xinhua) -- Nepal needs a transfer of
technology in many areas especially where the country has
export-oriented products with competitive advantages in the
international market, a senior government official said.
</P>
<P>
Education Minister Devi Prasad Ojha told the opening of a
regional seminar here Thursday that Nepal, like most developing
countries, depends heavily on foreign countries for technology in
the country's industrialization process.
</P>
<P>
Nepal still has backward types of technology in some areas and
worse still, these outdated technologies are running in an
effective way, he said.
</P>
<P>
He called on foreign technical experts to help improve Nepal's
existing technologies as Nepali technicians are familiar with them
and they can be handled at the local level.
</P>
<P>
The two-day seminar titled "Technological Capability Building
in Southeast Asian Region", was organized by the Royal Nepal
Academy for Science and Technology (RONAST) and was being attended
by about 45 experts from Bangladesh, China, India, Pakistan and
Thailand.  
