<HEADLINE> Myers the Last-gasp Hero for Bologna </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Carlton Myers kept Team System
Bologna in the hunt for a place in European basketball's Final
Four on Thursday, stopping an equaliser and then firing a
two-pointer in the final seconds against Barcelona, last year's
finalists.
</P>
<P>
With the home team leading the more favoured Spaniards 68-65,
the American prevented ex-Bologna playmaker Alexander Djordjevic
from netting a three-pointer and then raced up the court on the
rebound for the 70-65 win.
</P>
<P>
Barcelona led for the opening part of the first half and were
five points ahead after five minutes.
</P>
<P>
But Team System cut the gap, overtaking 37-33 at the break with
Myers providing 11 points and Eric Murdock the same.
</P>
<P>
The return leg is on Barcelona on Tuesday with a playoff in
Bologna if needed two days later. 
