<HEADLINE> U.N. to Help Thailand Implement Development Plan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, March 28 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations has signed a
cooperation agreement with Thailand to help the country carry out
its eighth national economic and social development plan, the
local press reported.
</P>
<P>
Thai Prime Minister Chavalit Yongchaiyudh and U.N.
representative Rafeeuddin Ahmed presided over the signing ceremony
at the government house on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
