development in local communities through shared visions and
objectives.
</P>
<P>
Pilot projects will be set up in some provinces like Phayao,
Petchaburi, Pattani and a few communities in Bangkok.
</P>
<P>
Initial activities will include the promotion of partnerships,
networking and community participation to reduce disparities and
poverty, and the development of local administrations.
</P>
<P>
The Thai government has set aside 20 million baht (800,000 U.S.
dollars) to back the pact while U.N. organizations in Bangkok have
allocated 12.5 million baht (500,000 dollars) to reinforce related
activities.  
