<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Export to UK Rises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 28 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's total export to
Britain rose to 380 million U.S. dollars last year, a 13 percent
increase over 1995, according to official figures released today.
</P>
<P>
The increase in exports was mainly attributed to the strong
performance of Sri Lanka's garment industry.
</P>
<P>
