<HEADLINE> Car Bomb Rocks Bulgarian Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SOFIA, March 27 (Xinhua) -- A powerful car bomb exploded in the
downtown Bulgarian capital of Sofia late Thursday but caused no
injures, state TV reported.
</P>
<P>
Police were quoted as saying that the blast destroyed a luxury
jeep and smashed the windows of some surrounding houses, many of
which host business offices.
</P>
<P>
The jeep owner was not immediately identified by police, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
The incident was now under investigation. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
