<DATE_TIME> 1997-03-28 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Latest Clash Kills 17 in Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Seventeen people were shot dead in
a gun battle in central Albania on Thursday, the heaviest toll
during the past two months in the Balkan state, Albanian news
agency ATA reported.
</P>
<P>
It said the killings began when 16 armed people went to the
village of Levan in central Albania and shot dead the chairman of
the council of elders of Levan before local inhabitants surrounded
the group and killed them all.
</P>
<P>
Much of southern Albania is under control of armed protesters,
who insisted that President Sali Berisha be resigned for the
collapse of popular savings schemes in January in which thousands
of Albanian families lost their savings.
</P>
<P>
More than 150 people have been killed in Albania, which has
been engulfed by chaos since this month caused by the collapse of
popular pyramid savings schemes in January. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
