<HEADLINE> Nicaraguan Plastic Arts University Opens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANAGUA, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Nicaragua's first plastic arts
university, "Armando Morales" School of Plastic Arts, will open in
this May in Granada, capital of the central namesake province.
</P>
<P>
The university was promoted by Dietmar Schonherr, president for
life of the Casa de los Tres Mundos Foundation, the sponsoring
institution, Granada Mayor Tatiana de Chamorro, and painter
Armando Morales.
</P>
<P>
The promoters said the institution of higher learning would
offer students two levels of study: two-year courses to obtain a
plastic arts diploma, and four-year courses in which students
would study engraving, sculpture, painting and computer-assisted
graphic design. 
</P>
