<HEADLINE> Peru to Restart Talks to Settle Hostage Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LIMA, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Direct dialogue between the Peruvian
government and the rebels holding 72 captives inside the Japanese
ambassador's residence will be restarted soon, but there will be
no release of the jailed rebels, President Alberto Fujimori said
today.
</P>
<P>
Fujimori said in a television statement that there would be a
meeting soon between government spokesman Domingo Palermo, and
Nestor Cerpa Cartolini, the head of the Tupac Amaru Revolutionary
Movement (MRTA) rebels.
</P>
<P>
Fujimori said the meeting would seek to define the possibility
of an agreement on more concrete bases.
</P>
<P>
"Although there are still some difficulties, there have been
important advances in the search for a peaceful solution," the
president said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
