<HEADLINE> Saudis Beat Bangladesh in Asian World Cup Qualifying </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIYADH, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Saudi Arabia scored three goals
against nil for a win over Bangladesh in the Group One Asian World
Cup qualifying Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
With the win, Saudi broke the deadlock with Malaysia to take
the top spot in the group as the other two members of Malaysia and
Chinese Taipei played a scoreless draw.
</P>
<P>
The Saudis, winners of Asian Cup last year, netted their first
strike only two minuets into the game through Ibrahim Al-Suwayed.
</P>
<P>
Despite a great save which denied a penalty kick from Khaled
Al-Timawy, Bangladesh's goalkeeper Ponir was not strong enough to
beat the eleven Saudi nationals.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the half break, Ponir was beaten the second time by
Obaid Al Doussary.
</P>
<P>
With 15 minutes into the second half, Bangladesh was reduced to
10 men after Mohammed Ahmed was sent off for a foul on Sami
Al-Jaber.
</P>
<P>
Abdullah Al-Jamaan scored 11 minutes before the game's end off
a pass from right-back Abdullah Shelia.
</P>
<P>
Saudi Arabia will face Malaysia on Saturday and a win will
award Saudi a spot in the second round. 
</P>
</TEXT>
