<TEXT>
<P>
-- The State Commission for Restructuring the Economy has
listed a number of major reforms of the country's economic
structure this year, with the reform of state-owned enterprises
serving as the top priority.
</P>
<P>
In line with the strategic objectives of China's Ninth
Five-year Plan (1996-2000), the reforms also cover investment
mechanisms, social security, housing, commodity circulation,
taxation, and banking.
</P>
<P>
-- Film-makers should produce more and better films that depict
socialist cultural and ethical progress, and gain more economic
returns while attaching importance to the social effect, said a
senior Party official.
</P>
<P>
Ding Guangen, member of the Political Bureau of the Communist
Party of China (CPC) Central Committee and also member of the
Central Committee's Secretariat, said at a three-day forum closed
yesterday that film-producers and government departments at all
levels produced more films that carry forward socialist cultural
and ethical progress, and quite a number of them gained popularity
over the past year.
</P>
<P>
 "Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- The Chinese Government is ready to work with the Bolivian
Government to develop long-term, stable and all-round friendship
and cooperative ties with an eye to the 21st century.
</P>
