president Lee Tung-hui was condemned yesterday by a Chinese
Foreign Ministry Spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said that China is firmly opposed to any
activities that could split the motherland.
</P>
<P>
"We are opposed to anyone who conducts activities that might
split the motherland and damage national unity anywhere," said the
spokesman.
</P>
<P>
-- China's campaign to relieve poverty, promote education and
technology, and improve the health of people in rural areas will
receive assistance from the United Nations Development Program
(UNDP).
</P>
<P>
One of the top priorities will be to start the first China
National UN Volunteers (UNV) program in April by supplying 700,000
U.S. dollars in financial assistance, which will enable Chinese
specialists to serve in their own country as national UNV.
</P>
