<HEADLINE> Japan Clouds Nepal in World Cup Qualifier </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Group favorite Japan reapt its
third straight victory by routing Nepal 6-0 in the Group Four
Asian World Cup qualifying in Muscat, Oman on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Japan had a dominating start and netted the opener in the 24th
minute by Hiroshi Nanami.
</P>
<P>
Yet the limelight was stolen by Takaya Takagi who had a
hat-trick performance in the second half to pace Japan for a
lop-sided victory with the other two goals netted by Norio Omura
and Yasuta Honda.
</P>
<P>
In the other game, Nabil Mubarak scored a goal in each half to
pace Oman for a 4-0 win over Macao.
</P>
<P>
Majdi Shabaan opened the scoring in the 31st minute and Mubarak
added the insurance three minutes before halftime. He scored his
second in the 56th and Al Tayeb Abdul Noor sealed the game in the
83rd.
</P>
<P>
Japan finished the first half with a perfect 3-0-0 record, with
the last six games to be resumed on June 22 in Japan.
</P>
<P>
Oman ranked second with two wins against one loss, while Macao
and Nepal tailed in the group with one point each.
</P>
<P>
Only the 10 group winners will advance to the second round of
the Asian qualifying to vie for three or four slots in the 1998
World Cup finals in France. 
</P>
</TEXT>
