<HEADLINE> Brazil's Poultry Exports Rise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's poultry exports
increased from 428,000 tons in 1995 to 568,000 tons, worth 840
million U.S. dollars, in 1996, a 32 percent increase.
</P>
<P>
Sales of poultry overseas will hit 1 billion dollars in 1997, a
19-percent increase over 1996, said Luiz Fernando Furlan, the
president of the Brazilian Association of Chicken Exporters.
</P>
<P>
"Poultry exports, which started 25 years ago, rank third in
Brazilian exports, surpassing other meat exports," said Furlan.
</P>
