<HEADLINE> Sa Pinto Faces Three-Year Ban </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Portuguese striker Sa Pinto faces
a three-year ban from football after attacking national coach
Arthur Jorge earlier this week.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old, who has now been dropped from the team to play
Northern Ireland in a World Cup qualifier this weekend in Belfast,
insisted on Wednesday that Jorge is to be blamed for his insult
first.
</P>
<P>
Sa Pinto claims that when he turned up for the team's final
training session before leaving for Northern Ireland, Jorge called
him "a son of a whore."
</P>
<P>
The Sporting Lisbon attacker immediately began punching and
kicking Jorge and had to be pulled away by fellow teammates.
</P>
<P>
The Portuguese Football Federation has opened an inquiry into
the incident and if Sa Pinto is found guilty could face a three
year ban. 
</P>
