<HEADLINE> Argentina Rejects Spanish Warrant Against Ex-Military Chief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Argentine Foreign Minister
Guido di Tella rejected here today a Spanish request for the
arrest of a former Argentine military chief of state.
</P>
<P>
Di Tella told the press that the international and provisional
warrant issued by Spanish Judge Baltazar Garzon against Leopoldo
Fortunato Galtieri was an excess of jurisdiction.
</P>
<P>
He also ruled out any dialogue on the matter with the Spanish
government.
</P>
<P>
Garzon ordered Tuesday the arrest of Galtieri to make him
answer questions about the alleged disappearance of 400 Spaniards
during the de facto Argentine government he headed from December
23, 1981, to June 17, 1982. 
</P>
</TEXT>
