<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Everton Manager Quits for Poor Showing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Due to poor results in the Premier
League, Joe Royle resigned on Thursday as manager of Everton Club.
</P>
<P>
After 31 games, Everton is five points above the relegation
zone with 13 losses, a dismaying contrast to neighbor Liverpool
which is racing against Manchester United for the League title.
</P>
<P>
"I have been disappointed by recent results and our current
league position," said Royle, a former Everton striker of the late
1960s and 70s. "Having spoken to the chairman, it has been agreed
we should part company by mutual consent."
</P>
<P>
Royle who capped England for six times, took the helm of
Everton in November 1994 when the club tailed in the League.
</P>
<P>
He guided Everton to be away from relegation and finished sixth
last season. 
</P>
</TEXT>
