<HEADLINE> China to Hold First Calligraphy Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, March 28 (Xinhua) -- Chinese artists will gather in
Tianjin this October to celebrate the country's first calligraphy
festival.
</P>
<P>
The event will showcase different schools of the art, which
originated thousands of years ago and is regarded as a national
treasure.
</P>
<P>
To create the art, calligraphers use traditional brushes and
ink to form pictographic characters on white paper, styling them
to look like abstract paintings.
</P>
<P>
Masterpieces can usually be auctioned for thousands of US
dollars on the international market.
</P>
<P>
The art has also been greatly developed in many Asian
countries, including Japan and Korea.  
</P>
