<HEADLINE> Hingis Beats Novotna to Advance to Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Martina Hingis fought off the
sizzling temperatures to seal a hard-earned victory over Jana
Novotna on Thursday and advanced to the final of the Lipton
Championships.
</P>
<P>
The top-seeded Hingis has now kept her winning streak to 25
matches by edging out third seed Novotna 6-3, 2-6, 6-4.
</P>
<P>
The 16-year-old Swiss, already assured of becoming the youngest
player to reach the number one ranking, has made to four finals
this year, winning them all.
</P>
<P>
Hingis will play the winner of Thursday's later semifinal
between fourth-seeded American Monica Seles and 11th seed Barbara
Paulus of Austria.
</P>
<P>
Hingis appeared to have the match in control early, breaking
Novotna for a 2-0 lead and won the first set 6-3 with a blistering
backhand up the line.
</P>
<P>
Novotna got the first break in the second set to lead 3-1 and
held onto the advantage, breaking Hingis again to take the set 6-2
with a forehand winner.
</P>
<P>
After that, both players left the court for the optional
10-minute break allowed under the rules during hot weather. It was
Hingis who came back more refreshed.
</P>
<P>
Hingis fought off break points in the eighth game with well
placed passing shots before breaking a weary Novotna for 5-4 and
going on to serve out the match with her first ace 6-4. 
</P>
</TEXT>
