<HEADLINE> Qiao Shi Meets with French National Assembly President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 27 (Xinhua) -- Qiao Shi, chairman of the Standing
Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC) of China, today
told Philippe Seguin, president of the French National Assembly,
that China has made great achievements in its construction of law.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with Seguin in the latter's official
residence, Qiao said that China wishes to make use of the
successful experience in law-making by developed countries in its
own construction of law.
</P>
<P>
He said that China will strengthen the work of law-making in
order to provide a good environment for reform, opening and
modernization construction.
</P>
<P>
He expressed his wish that through friendly exchanges, the NPC
and the French National Assembly will enhance mutual understanding
and learn from each other.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that the 5th Plenary Session of the 8th NPC has just
decided the main tasks, policies and measures for economic
construction and social development of China in 1997.
</P>
<P>
He said that China will unwaveringly carry forward reform,
expand opening and seek new achievements in socialist
modernization construction.
</P>
<P>
He said that the prosperity and progress of China have provided
the country with a great perspective and a good opportunity to
develop relations with all countries of the world in political,
economic, trade, scientific, technological and cultural fields.
</P>
<P>
Qiao also expressed his belief that under the joint efforts by
the two countries, the relations between China and France will
rise to a new higher level.
</P>
<P>
Seguin said that both he and the president of the French
Senate, Rene Monory, attach great importance to developing
relations with China, and wish to push forward Franco-Chinese
relations through their ties with the NPC of China.
</P>
<P>
At a dinner held in honor of Qiao Shi, Seguin noted that both
France and China attach great importance to their national
independence.
</P>
<P>
He said that France supports China's application for the
membership of the World Trade Organization (WTO), and it is glad
that China will become a member of the WTO soon.
</P>
<P>
Seguin said that Franco-Chinese relations have been developed
in the past few years, and that the forthcoming visit by President
Jacques Chirac to China will be a significant event in the
development of bilateral relations. 
</P>
