Sino-French relations and increase the friendly exchanges and
cooperations between the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that China and France share many common points. He
said that both countries cherish their own national independence,
oppose hegemonism, and share identical views on many international
issues.
</P>
<P>
He said that as permanent members of the United Nations
Security Council, China and France have responsibility for world
affairs.
</P>
<P>
Qiao said that China and France should establish from a
strategic point of view a lasting, steady and friendly
relationship of cooperation which is oriented toward the 21st
century, to push forward the trend of multipolarism in the world.
</P>
<P>
Qiao highly evaluated the contribution made by President Chirac
in enhancing Sino-French relations, and said that the forthcoming
visit by President Chirac to China will be an important event in
bilateral relations and will have important international impact
as well.
</P>
<P>
"We are looking forward to the visit by the president. We are
making preparations for the visit, and we believe that the visit
will be fully successful and will further push forward
cooperations between the two countries in political, economic,
scientific, technological and cultural fields," he said.
</P>
<P>
Qiao also conveyed the regards from President Jiang Zemin and
Premier Li Peng to President Chirac. 
